HEADWORD: Increpate
<hw>In"cre*pate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>increpatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>increpare</ets> to upbraid; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in, against + <ets>crepare</ets> to talk noisily.]</ety>
<def>To chide; to rebuke; to reprove.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Increpation</ent>⟦br⟧
